{
  "doc_id": "59299",
  "text": "Beyond the specific bioenergetic/biosynthetic demands of CSC, special classes of elite metabolites and the relative spatio-temporal abundance of common interpreters of the metabolic state that are critical factors for de/methylation, de/acetylation, or de/ phosphorylation dynamics in the nuclear epigenome (e.g., acetyl-CoA, α-ketoglutarate, NAD+, FAD, ATP, or S-adenosylmethionine), might be causally involved in the redirection of normal and non-CSC toward a CSC-like state [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . We have coined the term metabostemness to describe the metabolic parameters that causally control the epi-transcriptional programs defining CSC states [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] .",
